updatesFromCustomers.text: This is the silver statue of Lord Ganesh ( Ashok Vinayak ) which is kept inside the guthi Ghar for the whole year. This statue is placed inside the temple on the 9th and 10th day of dashain (i.e. Nawami & Dashami) and on the 11th day (i.e. Ekadashi) the statue is carried in a chariot and circulated throughout the old alleys of Kathmandu.

updatesFromCustomers.text:
The temple is about 1.5 km inside from Dhungedhara Ringroad on the way to Raniban.
Compared to previous years this temple has been well managed and renovated now. It often gets crowded during festivals.
This is the Hindu temple of Lord Krishna and Radha.
It is one of the famous landmarks of this area.
